-- Reliance Communications Plans to Sell Its Tower Business to GTL, ET Says
-- Natalie Obiko Pearson
-- 2010-06-27T03:02:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-27/reliance-communications-plans-to-sell-its-tower-business-to-gtl-et-says.html

          
          
             Reliance Communications Ltd. ,
India’s second-largest wireless carrier, may sign an agreement
as early as today to sell its mobile-phone tower business to GTL
Infrastructure Ltd. for $6 billion, the Economic Times reported.  
 The deal would transfer Reliance Communication’s 50,000
towers and $3 billion of debt to GTL, said the report, which
cited a person it did not identify. GTL is India’s largest
independent operator of mobile-phone towers.  
 Reliance Communications spokesman Guarav Wahi did not
answer a call to his cell phone requesting comment. Calls to
GTL’s headquarters in Mumbai were not answered.  
 Reliance Communications, controlled by billionaire  Anil Ambani , said on June 14 it planned to spin off its  Reliance
Infratel Ltd.  tower unit and use the proceeds to pay debt.  
 GTL in January agreed to buy 17,500 transmission sites from
Aircel Ltd. for 84 billion rupees to help it double its network
in India. American Tower Corp.  
